I don't have a fancy magelo profile so I'll just mention what I'm currently wearing:<br>
<br>
A full set of Enchanted Dwarven Platemail armor (except for my head, I wear an Incarnadine Helmet)<br>
Velium Fire Wedding rings and Cougar Claw earrings.<br>
A pair of SCHW's<br>
A Frostbringer and a Venemous Axe of the Velium Brood (Will be swapped out with a Club of the Ice Ocean once I hit lv51)<br>
And a Black Acrylia Halberd<br>
<br>
That's pretty much it...I was told to look for Brellium Plate gear but it seems awfully expensive for one who has only around 1k in his bank and only income being whatever he picks up during EXP groups.<br>
<br>
Is it too early for me to start doing Thurg plate quests? (I have no idea how to start/do these whatsoever and I am unguilded) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jugerrnaut>Jugerrnaut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/03 5:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5557.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Time to upgrade?</span><hr size=1> First upgrade i would recommend is your worn hate item, need better than that most definitely.<br>
<br>
Go to Allakhazam's and research (guessing you'll go dorf faction first) Thurg armor, print off a list of the required gems, then start building groups for Velks, you're at a great level for exp in there, and the gems you need, well, alot of them will come out of Velks from the spiders.<br>
<br>
Your next step once you've collected the gems you will need, or if you skip this part and simply buy them, (expensive), then start building or getting into Kael Arena groups and pray for plate drops and lucky randoms, this is very time consuming, but, the faction required will take alot of time, so theres really no short cutting it, unless you end up max Ally and havent won any corroded plat armor drops, then the purchase of MQ plate drops might be your next option. You are currently a little low for the Arena in level, but if you gain a few levels in Velks from the spideys, you're golden. Don't expect to be MT'ing Arena group at 50 tho, it's just not a good idea and definitely not mana efficient, and always always always have a slower, K?<br>
<br>
Good luck, much much more detailed info can be found on AllaK's... <p> Myrmidon



